<TITLE> DCCI asks banks to stay open this Saturday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 16 (bdnews24.com)The Dhaka Chamber of Commerce and Industry (DCCI) has urged high street banks to keep their branches open on Saturday, ahead of the Eid-ul-Fitr break, to allow businessmen to deposit their takings. "Banks and other organisations will close from September 20 to 22 for Eid-ul-Fitr. DCCI thinks businessmen could experience problems depositing their takings if the banks remain closed for so long," a DCCI press release issued Wednesday said. In the interest of the business community, we strongly urge the Bangladesh Bank to instruct commercial banks to open on Sept 19, said the statement. b
